~ 0 TAXI CAB~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
The taxi system allows players to get from point A to point B at a quick and
typically precise rate, but with the cost of cab fare. 
#n
For simplicity's sake, all cab fares are 10 dollars. 
#n
Not everywhere on the map can be driven directly to by a taxi cab. There are
many locations, hideaways, easter eggs and simply not taxi-able places that
need to be explored, located and either walked to on foot or driven to in a
personal vehicle #g(help vehicle)#n.
#n
#GSyntax:#n
#n
#wtaxi            #g-- #n"Taxi" without an argument displays a list of areas and 
#n                    destinations.
#wtaxi <area> <##> #g-- #nTakes a taxi cab to the specified area and destination.
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
~ 0 PREGNANCY BREED~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#GSystem Summary and Rules#n
#n
The pregnancy code exists to track generational lines and realistically
address the biological complexity of physical relationships. In layman's
terms, if you're roleplaying sex, fading it to black or otherwise, the breed
command must be used without exception.
#n
Staff take no stance on mudsex one way or the other. Adults have sex; it's a
reasonable expectation that at some point our players will write it into 
their relationships. Write about whatever you like, but please use the 
appropriate command(s)!
#n
Birth control and condoms are coded into the game and should be purchased and
used prior to entering the breed command if contraceptives are roleplayed. An
assumed use of "phantom" contraceptives is against the rules, and not accepted
as a reason why the breed command wasn't used.
#n
The characters created as a result of pregnancy can be used by either mother
or father as an NPC; their pfiles should be given descriptions and roomdescs
prior to joining roleplay. Children are allowed into the same scenes as the
parent puppeting them; we do not consider child pfiles to count as multiplay.
#n
The Lost greatly celebrate and revere the incredibly rare child born to their
kind; while the code acknowledges the near-impossible chances of a Changeling
being able to conceive, it can (in legendarily rare circumstances) be done.
#n
#gNote(s):#n The breed command does not need to be used for same-sex couples, as
its purpose is to check for pregnancy. Coded pregnancy lasts approximately
four real life months. 
#n
#GCommands:#n
#n
#wbreed <name> #g-- #nStarts a behind-the-scenes roll for pregnancy.
#wuse <item>   #g-- #nAdds the "contraceptive" affect to the person that used the
                item. Must be used before "breed" to work. When breed is used,
                the affect is removed. Contraceptives are single-use.
#wbirth <name> #g--#n When you go into labour you will be prompted. Birth will
                create a pfile with the name you choose, and genes based upon
                mom and dad. To set their password, log in with their name and
                enter a password when prompted.
#n
#RDo not use the breed command on anyone as a joke, as an OOC mechanic or in any
situation where roleplay has not necessitated it.#n
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
~ 0 PATHFIND PATHFINDING~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
The pathfinding code maps out directions from your present location to a
targeted individual. This is of especial importance to the visually impaired,
and offered as an alternative to the ascii map (help map) code.
#n
The pathfinding output is extremely simple, and this is was purposeful design
choice. Screenreaders should be able to report the directions required to get
to anyone currently logged into the game. 
#n
Check "where" to see a list of players who are online, make sure they are in a
place you would like your character to join, and work your pathfinding magic!
#n
#GSyntax:#n
#n
#wpathfind <player> #g-- #nProvides a list of directions from your current location
#n                     to the targeted player. 
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
~ 0 CASINO SLOT SLOTS~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
Our slot machines have ten possible results in each roll: cherry, plum,
grape, watermelon, orange, lemon, bar, double bar, triple bar, or seven. 
Getting three of the same results in a row (this counts diagonally,
horizontally, or vertically) wins.  The amount you win from that particular
result depends on what it is, the result calculations are as follows:
#x
#RCHERRY#n (any) (any)  - Win your bet + 1/4 (horizontally only).
#RCHERRY CHERRY#n (any) - Win your bet + 1/2 (horizontally only).
#RCHERRY#n x3           - Win the amount you bet.
#pPLUM#n x3             - Win double the amount you bet.
#PGRAPE#n x3            - Win triple the amount you bet.
#GWATERMELON#n x3       - Win the amount you bet x 4.
#oORANGE#n x3           - Win the amount you bet x 5.
#yLEMON#n x3            - Win the amount you bet x 6.
#gBAR#n x3              - Win the amount you bet x 7.
#C2#cBAR#n x3             - Win the amount you bet x 8.
#G3#gBAR#n x3             - Win the amount you bet x 9.
#BSEVEN#n x3            - Win the amount you bet x 10.
#BSEVEN#n x6            - Jackpot, varies (must be aligned diagonally, both
#n                      ways making an 'X').
#n
#GSyntax:#n
#n
#wslot play 25 #g-- #nPlays the slot machine with a bet of 25 pounds.
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
~ 0 MONEY CURRENCY WORTH PAYCHEQUE~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
The currency system involves the use of pounds to pay for whatever your
character might want or need. On Penny Dreadful, your weekly paycheque
directly reflects your rating in the Resources Merit. 
#n
You will not automatically collect a paycheque -- when your timer expires, you
will receive a notification (if you are online at the time) stating that you
can collect again. Inactive characters do not automatically collect paycheques
and stockpile money while away; you must be online and enter the command to 
collect your weekly funds.
#n
Your money is used to purchase items, order drinks, pay for cabs (pending) and
contend with a potentially endless list of uses.  
#n
You can give money to other people with the "give" command, just like with
items. 
#n
#GSyntax:#n
#n
#wworth                    #g-- #nDisplay your character's current worth in pounds.
#wpaycheque                #g-- #nCollect your character's weekly pay check. 
#wgive ## pound[s] [target] #g-- #nHand over some pound coins to the target.
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
~ 0 HUNT~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
The Hunt code is provided for Changelings to regain Glamour by rolling
through one of several methods (with success determining how much or
little Glamour is gained). 
#n
Changelings with the Harvest Merit may also use the code to regain a number
of Glamour points equal to their rating in Harvest per day.
#
#GSyntax:#n
#n
#whunt <type> <method>#g -- #nAttempt to hunt for a specific kind of Glamour using
#n                        specified method.
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
~ 0 FORAGE~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
One of the most potent tools a Changeling has at their disposal is the
collection and use of Goblin Fruit. Fruits may be foraged from the Hedge
with the proper skill set -- a Changeling must know what they're looking
for and still succeed in locating the proper fruit or herb.
#n
Changelings may forage for Goblin Fruit twice per day (this is code enforced).
#n
#GSyntax:#n
#n
#wforage <herb/fruit> <type> #g-- #nAttempt to forage for the target herb or fruit.
#n
You can enter "forage" with no argument to see the table of fruits and herbs
that can be foraged. You must be in the Hedge to forage for Goblin Fruit.
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
~ 0 RAT~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
Changelings and Ensorcelled characters cannot use modern implements in the
Hedge. As such, they have developed a means of contacting one another via
long-distances without leaving the Hedge; the rats of the London Underground
are well-trained and recognize the Lost for what they are. In exchange for a
pittance in Glamour (occasionally in exchange for future favors or a moment's
attention) the hedge rats will deliver items or notes to other Hedge-dwelling
individuals.
#n
#GSyntax:#n
#n
#wrat <item> <recipient> #g-- #nDelivers the specified item to the specified target.
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n~ 0 APPLY PERFUME COLOGNE WASH~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
Perfumes and colognes can be purchased from stores and used to make yourself
smell fantastic. When a scent is worn, it will display to anyone who enters
the room with you. 
#n
#GSyntax:#n
#n
#wapply <scent>#g --#n Applies the scent to your character.
#wwash         #g --#n Washes off perfume or cologne (must be bathroom)
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
~ 0 ORDER BAR~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
