~ 0 SNEAK HIDE SNEAKING HIDING STEALTH~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
Sneaking and hiding are both mundane aspects of the Stealth Skill. Hide has a
lower threshold for success, and allows the Stealth user to remain still and
hidden in a single room. Sneak requires a higher success threshold, and allows
the Stealth user to move from room to room without alerting others to their
arrival or presence.
#n
Stealth and Hide are both automatically contested by others. If you have 
entered "look" you have already rolled to contest the stealth success of any
hidden individual. Sneak is contested by others when you first enter the
room with them. 
#n
#GSyntax:#n
#n
#whide#g  --#n Rolls to attempt to hide in the room. Breaks if you travel into any
#n         direction. 
#wsneak#g --#n Rolls to attempt to sneak, making your arrival/departure hidden and
#n         hiding you from the room(s). 
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
~ 0 PICK LOCKPICK LOCKPICKING~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
Lockpicking allows characters with the Larceny Skill to pick and open locked
doors. A roll is performed behind the scenes (Dexterity + Larceny), and with
a minimum number of successes, the lock will open. Lockpicking can only be
performed once every 30 seconds. Picking locks is an In-Character act, and is
of course illegal. Take into account where you are before picking a lock;
Staff may drop a policeman onto your head in the right (wrong?) circumstances.
#n
#RThe pick command is logged.#n
#n
#GSyntax:#n
#n
#wpick <direction> #g-- #nAttempts to pick the lock in the indicated direction.
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
~ 0 SPY SCAN~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
The spy and scan commands, while related, have two moderately different uses.
Spy is considered to be an IC mechanic (and rolls behind the scenes each time
it is used to determine the success your character has), and has a range of
several rooms from your character. Scan is a take on the classic scan command,
which displays only those in your character's immediate vicinity (and requires
no roll).
#n
#GSyntax:#n
#n
#wscan            #g--#n Display characters in your immediate vicinity.
#wspy <direction> #g--#n Roll to detect characters at varying distances from you.
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
~ 0 MOTLEY MOTLEYS MTALK~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
The Motley code is designed to allow characters to form their own Motleys,
assign their own leadership, appoint a secondary leader, induct their own
members, and create their own Motley channel without Staff intervention.
#n
Motleys must always be formed as a result of In-Character activities. They
are not OOC constructs and will not be used as such.
#n
Mortals can join Motleys with certain conditions. See the House Rules for
details!#n
#n
#RWhen a Motley is formed, put up a Request Board note with the details of
your Motley Pledge and all founding members.#n
#n
#GSyntax:#n
#wmotley#g  -- #nDisplays a menu with commands for non-Motley members, and details
           about your Motley if you are already a member of one.
#wmtalk #g  -- #nChat to members of your Motley via your Motley channel.

#wmotley found <name> #g  --#n Found a Motley with the specified name.
#wmotley ready #g         --#n Finalize a Motley and add to to the roster(s).
#wmotley info #g          --#n Display details about your Motley if you are already
                         a member of one.
#wmotley leave #g         --#n Leave your current Motley.
#wmotley outcast <name> #g--#n Outcast an individual from your Motley.
#n
#GStaff:
#n
#wmotlist#g -- #nDisplays a list of online characters and their Motleys.
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
~ 0 STAFF STANDARDS~
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#n Innocence Lost RPI#y -#n HELP DATABASE
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
#GGENERAL STANDARDS#n

#g1.#n Staff may not take any action which affects their character alts, up to and
including handling their own purchase requests or issuing weekly XP.

#g2.#n You will not be able to make everyone happy. Don't try to. Do what is best
for the overall population. On your Staff account(s), you are to be neutral 
and courteous at all times. 

#g3.#n Do not champion any game-related cause from your Staff account if it has 
any connection or perceived connection to your alt(s). Your influence as Staff
cannot be used to support your personal playstyle or character goals. Use your
player account to express opinions of that nature. This applies to the MUD, 
forum, and wiki talk pages. 

#g4.#n You are required to be intimately familiar with the House Rules and abide
by them. 

#g5.#n Staff may have alts in Court Monarch positions only if there are no players
interested in the role. Players are not expected to unseat you; when the 
situation arises that a player could fill the Monarch position, you are 
expected to come up with and execute a viable exit strategy. Go into any IC 
leadership role aware that it will be temporary. 

#g6.#n Give everyone the benefit of the doubt. Patience, understanding and 
compromise are essential; if it doesn't violate a rule, you have no authority
over it. Forward gray areas to Merry. 

#g7.#n There will always be somebody that just rubs you wrong. Always be ready to
give yourself an offline time-out to cool down, and ask another Staff member 
to handle potentially contentious situations with them.

#g8.#n Check the request board when you log in. If there is something on there
that you can handle, do so. 

#g9.#n Absolutely no information that you gain as a Staff member is to be leaked
beyond Staff channels.

#g10.#n The "snoop" and "log" commands are disabled for a reason. We do not spy on
players. Do not ever enter the IC grid on your Staff account while invisible. 

#GCHANNEL DECORUM#n

#g1.#n The Story channel is not an outlet for venting poison about players. Keep 
it positive and constructive, or don't say it at all. 

#g2.#n Staff are not to swear over OOC or hnet. Do not engage in arguments with 
players over any public or private channel. 

#g3.#n If you're online and visible, you will monitor and handle request channel
needs. 
#g--------------------------------------------------------------------------------#n
