~ 0 DISCLAIMER~
#r   .-----------------------------------------------------------------------.
#r  /#R                         Penny Dreadful Disclaimer#r                       \
#r /---------------------------------------------------------------------------\
#r/     #ROOC Channel #r  #R Adult Content#r   #R Harassment #r  #R Parents of Minors#r     \
#r|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------#r|#n
#r|#G OOC Channel#g:#n The OOC channel is a not-oft filtered mode of communication.   #r|#n
#r|#n The Administration may on occasion request that certain topics be dropped   #r|#n
#r|#n or that open disputes between players cease, but for the most part there is #r|#n
#r|#n an "anything goes" attitude that we strive to maintain on PD. As a result,  #r|#n
#r|#n content frequently strays into what some may find offensive. Some players   #r|#n
#r|#n choose to keep their OOC channel turned off to avoid viewing what they      #r|#n
#r|#n find objectionable. To turn your OOC channel off, type channel -ooc and     #r|#n
#r|#n -omote.                                                                     #r|#n
#r|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------#r|#n
#r|#G Adult Content#g:#n Penny Dreadful MUD is for adult participants only. Many      #r|#n
#r|#n In-Character scenarios are alarming or offensive.                           #r|#n
#r|#n                                                                             #r|#n
#r|#n Though you certainly have the option to log out of Penny at any time,       #r|#n
#r|#n you may not opt out of story arcs or In-Character situations you object to  #r|#n
#r|#n on an OOC (or IC for that matter) basis. This means that anything can       #r|#n
#r|#n happen to your character, it does #Rnot#n mean that you have to actively        #r|#n
#r|#n participate in a pose-by-pose roleplay scene describing it. A Fade to Black #r|#n
#r|#n (FtB) is perfectly acceptable to handle disturbing or otherwise             #r|#n
#r|#n objectionable In-Character moments if one or more players are uncomfortable #r|#n
#r|#n with the content. By Fading to Black, it will be discussed OOCly what       #r|#n
#r|#n happened, rather than written out descriptively In-Character.               #r|#n
#r|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------#r|#n
#r|#G Harassment#g:#n On Penny Dreadful MUD we define harassment as repeated          #r|#n
#r|#n attempts, successful or otherwise, to contact a player after he or she has  #r|#n
#r|#n made it clear he does not wish to be contacted by a certain individual. If  #r|#n
#r|#n a player has OOCly told you to leave them alone and you persist, you are    #r|#n
#r|#n harassing that player.                                                      #r|#n
#r|#n                                                                             #r|#n
#r|#n In-Character interactions between players are an entirely separate affair   #r|#n
#r|#n from their OOC relationship. Unless the Storytellers have reason to suspect #r|#n
#r|#n a player is using their OOC dislike of a player to influence their In-      #r|#n
#r|#n Character behavior toward them, there is no such thing as "In-Character     #r|#n
#r|#n harassment." Do not report that a maniac is ICly stalking you around the    #r|#n
#r|#n city and you want him to stop. That is not harassment, it is roleplay.      #r|#n
#r|#n                                                                             #r|#n
#r|#n If you are being harassed please keep a screenshot of your interactions     #r|#n
#r|#n with the offender and submit it in a PM to Merry on the community forums.   #r|#n
#r|#n Behavior of the OOCly harassing variety almost without fail results in the  #r|#n
