~ 0 REC RECOMMENDATION RECOMMENDATIONS RECS~
#g   .-----------------------------------------------------------------------.
#g  /#G                           XP Recommendations                            #g\
#g /---------------------------------------------------------------------------\
#g/#G Guidelines#g:                                                                 \
#g|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------#g|#n
#g|#n Players may submit an unlimited number of total recs per day. However, they #g|#n
#g|#n may only rec someone's character one time per day. If PlayerA is playing    #g|#n
#g|#n his mortal character John and has a scene with Jebediah, he can rec Jebediah#g|#n
#g|#n one time that day on John. PlayerA then logs into his vampire, Bill, and has#g|#n
#g|#n another scene with Jebediah. PlayerA can rec Jebediah from Bill, too. If    #g|#n
#g|#n PlayerA has 5 scenes with Jebediah while logged into John, however, he may  #g|#n
#g|#n still only rec him once that day. In this respect alt characters are        #g|#n
#g|#n considered wholly separate.                                                 #g|#n
#g|#n                                                                             #g|#n
#g|#n Refrain from giving us only a summary of why you enjoyed a character's      #g|#n
#g|#n roleplay and not submitting the pose itself, as we won't be able to award   #g|#n
#g|#n XP if we haven't read a pose from the character. Players are encouraged to  #g|#n
#g|#n add a note to the end of the recommended pose to explain why they liked it, #g|#n
#g|#n but it is not required.                                                     #g|#n
#g|#n                                                                             #g|#n
#g|#n The pose you recommend for another character should be a good piece of      #g|#n
#g|#n writing - the best in that scene offered by the player. Do not recommend    #g|#n
#g|#n one-liners for the sake of recommending. The player will not earn XP for it.#g|#n
#g|#n It is also very frowned upon to simply recommend the first pose a player    #g|#n
#g|#n writes in a scene. Wait until the end of the scene and select the best pose,#g|#n
#g|#n don't just get recommending out of the way because you're too lazy to take  #g|#n
#g|#n some time after the scene to find the best (and most likely to get max XP)  #g|#n
#g|#n pose.                                                                       #g|#n
#g|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------#g|#n
#g|#G Syntax#g:                                                                     #g|#n
#g|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------#g|#n
#g|#n rec <player> <pose>                                                         #g|#n
#g|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------#g|#n
#g|#G XP Rewards#g:                                                                 #g|#n
#g|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------#g|#n
#g|#n XP is rewarded for recommendations every Friday. Individual poses earn from #g|#n
#g|#n 2 to 4 XP. The top three recommendations earned by your character that week #g|#n
#g|#n are added up, and the XP doled out. For example, players submitted 5 recs   #g|#n
#g|#n for Jaime this week. The first pose earned 2 XP, the second 3, the third 2, #g|#n
#g|#n the fourth 3, and the fifth 4. The top three poses are worth 3, 3, and 4,   #g|#n
#g\#n which means Jaime earns a total of 10 XP that week.                         #g/
#g '---------------------------------------------------------------------------'#n

